Did you know your skin health is directly linked to the fabric used to create your outfit?

Wearing the wrong material can cause irritation, acne, rashes—even infections. But there’s a smarter, skin-friendly alternative: LIVA fabric. 🌿

Crafted from plant-based fibres, LIVA is breathable, ultra-soft, and gentle on your skin—perfect for all-day comfort in any season. Bonus? It’s eco-conscious and sustainably made, so your style choices stay kind to the planet too.

Next time you shop, look for the LIVA pink tag on the garments—because your skin (and the earth) deserve the very best.

"NAD (nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide) is a coenzyme involved in several essential biological functions, including collagen production, memory, ATP generation and more," explains Dr Geerika Srivastava, dermatologist and founder Influennz Clinic. "It's the only known molecule that directly activates longevity proteins called sirtuins, potentially contributing to increased lifespan." In theory, boosting NAD+ levels could help improve skin function, texture and resilience, offering deeper benefits than surface-level hydration or exfoliation. But how it's delivered makes all the difference. VOGUE INDIA 26TH MAY, 2025'.

Aging gracefully is all about adapting your skincare routine to your skin’s evolving needs. Here’s a decade-wise breakdown to keep your skin radiant:

👩‍🔬 Late 20s: Start retinol early (0.2%) to boost collagen. Prevention is key.
👩‍🔬 30s: Upgrade to skin cycling, add peptides, and step up your retinol game (up to 0.5%).
👩‍🔬 40s & 50s: Don’t skip hyaluronic acid, vitamin C, E, and higher strength retinol (0.5%+).

📌 Your skin evolves—your skincare should too.
